The Minister of Foreign Affairs, Mr Geoffrey Onyeama, said that the Federal Government has evacuated 167 Nigerians from South Africa. In a tweet via his official twitter handle, the Minister said that the evacuees had already departed the O.R. Tambo International Airport in Johannesburg and are expected to arrive at the Nnamdi Azikiwe Airport before proceeding to Lagos. The tweet reads: “@flyairpeace conveying 167 Nigerians just departed O.R. Tambo International Airport Johannesburg, South Africa for the Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport, Abuja. “45 passengers will disembark in Abuja, and thereafter the plane will leave for Murtala Muhammed International Airport, Ikeja, Lagos with 122 passengers.” Dear our valued reader, we would like to hear your view about a membership club that we plan to launch. Kindly help us fill this survey. 268 Nigerians arrive from China P/H, Abuja, Lagos among 10 worst airports in Africa - Survey COVID-19: 160 stranded Nigerians arrive Abuja from US